highlights.description: Had an experience of being an out-group in her own neighborhood, confronted the girls that were bothering her and voiced that she was a member of the community.  A pivotal moment in her life. --> Update: I thought this was worth listening to because those that encounter these experiences are usually not white women.
Diversity fosters a sense of community, in this context.
On the importance of bodegas in NYC and how this bodega is part of fostering community within the neighborhood.
Access to bodies of water in the city are limited.
On the harsh reality of gentrification for low-income families.
On the issue of low-income and communities of color not having access to higher quality food and a better neighborhood without being subjugated to gentrification.
Inclusion of democratic processes in neighborhoods is more difficult for immigrants whom are not citizens.  Not being able to vote obscures their voice.
Low-income communities have less options for nutritious food because it is harder for smaller stores (i.e. bodegas) to provide these options for clients.
It is difficult to genuinely care for kids in the neighborhood because it might be perceived as impertinent to their parents.

One way to incentivize youth to be active is through arts and sports programs.  Absent these programs (because of lack of funds) students might be less likely to stay in school and more likely to remain in poverty.
There is an unequal distribution of funds towards schools, in turn this further exacerbates inequality.
Health disparities in the Bronx intersect with disparities across other areas such as education and income.
Homeless people are neglected and should also be listened to. Here, the individual made D feel visible and heard even if it was only for a moment.
There are more resources to help rehabilitate people with schizophrenia.  They have more resources which allows them to receive more humane treatment.
Her neighborhood seems less safe when people are under the influence of alcohol.
On an important initiative that works with bodegas on providing healthier options in stores that are convenient to people in the neighborhood.
Shares a comparable experience related to the hearth snippet.  Where this experience outside of NYC may not be as relatable depending on where in the states one is located (urban vs. rural.)
The facilitator does a good job at reorienting the conversation towards the hearth snippet.
